<li><a href="/wiki/Stuart_Hall_(cultural_theorist)" title="Stuart Hall (cultural theorist)">S. Hall</a>, R. Williams and <a href="/wiki/E._P._Thompson" title="E. P. Thompson">E. P. Thompson</a> (eds.) <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=New_Left_May_Day_Manifesto&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="New Left May Day Manifesto (page does not exist)">New Left May Day Manifesto</a>.</i> London, May Day Manifesto Committee, 1967. R. Williams (ed.) <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=May_Day_Manifesto&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="May Day Manifesto (page does not exist)">May Day Manifesto</a>,</i> Harmondsworth, Penguin, 1968, 2nd edition.</li>
<li><i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Drama_in_Performance_(book_by_Raymond_Williams)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Drama in Performance (book by Raymond Williams) (page does not exist)">Drama in Performance (book by Raymond Williams)</a>,</i> revised edition. New Thinkers Library, C. A. Watts, 1954</li>
<li><i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Drama_from_Ibsen_to_Brecht&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Drama from Ibsen to Brecht (page does not exist)">Drama from Ibsen to Brecht</a>,</i> London, Chatto and Windus, 1968. Reprinted, London, Hogarth Press, 1987.</li>
